        "body2": "RANCHI: BJP's astounding victory in the Uttar Pradesh assembly polls seems to have triggered the revival of Ram Janmabhoomi campaign of the Vishwa Hindu Parishad. The outfit's international joint general secretary Surendra Kumar Jain on Friday said no more delay in the construction of the temple in Ayodhya will be tolerated. VHP plans to hold awareness programmes across the nation from March 28 to April 10 to build a consensus on the proposed temple. \"VHP will organize awareness-building events across 6,000 blocks, 500 districts and 44 regional centres. We will unite Hindus and nationalists and together we shall pledge for the Ram temple construction,\" Jain said.\"VHP and the Hindu community at large will not tolerate any further delay on the construction of Ram Janmabhoomi temple. Now, BJP has won the UP elections and time is right for the Centre to enact a law to legalize the temple construction and remove all hurdles,\" said Jain, who was in Ranchi on Friday. Jain had visited a VHP training camp at Bokaro earlier.Calling the construction of the temple at Ayodhya a matter of national pride, Jain that it was the Mughal emperor Babur who had built the mosque over the Ram temple as a mark of his victory. He said: \"Babri masjid was a symbol of our defeat and shame. Building a temple at Ram Janmabhoomi will make the pseudo-secularists redundant and will be according to the Hindu wave that is sweeping the country. BJP's victory at the UP polls is an indication of this wave and the public sentiments. Building the temple will speed up development as it will put an end to jihad and sideline these pseudo-secularists.\"\"Construction of the Ram temple at the site where Babri masjid was built is essential to wipe out the symbol of slavery which Babur had imposed on us. Wiping out such symbols of slavery after achieving Independence has been practiced for long in various countries across the globe. In Warsaw, Petrograd, all symbols of dominance were removed as the people there rebuilt their churches in those places and when India gained independence the Somnath temple was built, in Delhi George Pancham's idol was replaced with that of Mahatma Gandhi and Queen Victoria's image was replaced with Swami Shraddhanand's idol. Now, Aurangzeb Road in Delhi too has been renamed to Dr APJ Abdul Kalam,\" Jain added.", 
